messages.message: Below some direct client feedback, who tested completely without our guidance. We have the samples as well they sent us. Note, this is a major insurer who just tested it out
@Varun Jain @avi I'll forward the email with samples to you for further analysis
@Bas can you please include me for any enterprise feedback?

thank you! @Bas do you know what type of documents they try to extract? it seems to be some name plate photos?

we definitely support batch processing -- i think they tried Converse; but they are actually looking for something more like Build which I guess is what he means but "support of batch" as in running a query on all photos instead of one at a time.

@Kerry they are pictures of boiler plates. This company inspects equipment, like boilers. They insure them also. The company is literally called "Hartford Steam Boiler" or HSB. One of the largest warranty, equipment insurance, and equipment inspection companies in the world. This is their Canada branch. You're right regarding batch. I think this is a subtle feedback we have seen before, that it is not always obvious to the first user how and/or if you can build this into a workflow. As most people start in converse, a subsequent prompt in the converse experience to lift those fields into a workflow automation could be very cool
